> This delicious Spiced Roasted Cauliflower Pilaf has been expertly designed by our chefs as a lighter option to help with a balanced lifestyle.

== Spiced Roasted Cauliflower ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle.

Halve any large @cauliflower florets{300%g}. Pop the cauliflower onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @North Indian style spice mix{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Rice ==

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When there are ~{2%minutes} left, add the @peas{120%g} to the rice and boil for the remaining time.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Korma Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the garlic and @korma curry paste{50%g}. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @onion marmalade{30%g} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount). Bring to the boil and cook until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Stir the cooked rice and peas into the korma mixture.

Add a splash of @water{} if needed.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== To Serve ==

Share the Indian inspired pilaf between your #bowls.

Top with the spiced roasted cauliflower.

Finish with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and a sprinkling of the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g}.

Enjoy!